EE16A, easily. I've taken both. I got an A in ee16a and A- in data100 but data100 was a much, much, much easier class. Even though you've taken 54 it'll still be difficult.

----------------

Agree that EE16A is "more difficult." However, one point to mention is that Data 100 grades on a raw scale, while EE16A bins the classes, so it could be a little harder to get a good grade in Data 100 given your experience.

children.subject: 2 projects, you mean. And HW6 is harder than the projects tbh Lol. And DS100 makes a good 3rd tech i think to round out schedules, but isn't heavy enough to warrant being a time sink.
Also on hws: 90% of it is easy and breeze through it in 10 mins, then theres always 1 or 2 problems that have the most intricate solution ever / are super buggy.

16A in my opinion has 5x the workload of data 100. I think both have conceptually tough 2nd halves, but 16A has really confusing weekly problem sets, boring labs if you're not interested in EE, and a ton of discussion and practice.

Data 100 has 6 hws, very straightforward, 1 easy discussion per week, and 2 hws that are basically just 1.5x workload of a hw. With that being said, if you're looking for easy tech elective, take data 100. If you're optimizing learning and are willing to take 3 tough techs a semester, avoid data 100.
